The paper proposes a method for learning the structures of feedforward neural networks (FNNs) based on hierarchical latent tree models (HLTMs), which are a type of probabilistic graphical model (PGM). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary sub-category for papers on deep learning and PGMs. 

The paper also presents extensive empirical results on classification tasks, which suggests that it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). However, since the focus of the paper is on structure learning for deep models, rather than specific applications or techniques, these sub-categories are less likely than cs.LG.
